SIMPLE: outlaugh
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outlaugh
<hw>Out*laugh"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
surpass or outdo in laughing.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To laugh (one) out of a purpose, principle, etc.; to
discourage or discomfit by laughing; to laugh down.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His apprehensions of being <qex>outlaughed</qex> will force him to
continue in a restless obscurity.</q> <rj><qau>Franklin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outlaw</ent>⟦br⟧
